    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, AND BUMPER - WorkStar&#8482; Series Starting March 2007 - REMOVE AND INSTALL
        PROCEDURES - Hood Mirror
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Hood Mirror</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Hood Mirror - Removal</title>
            <figure id="f0901127" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901127.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Hood Mirrors</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RIGHT HOOD MIRROR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LEFT HOOD MIRROR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HOOD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the hood is equipped with sound insulation, gently pry the sound insulation away from
                    the hood mirror mounting hardware as needed.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove three nuts and washers from inside of the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the hood mirror from the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Hood Mirror - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the hood mirror on the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure hood mirror to the hood with three washers and nuts. Torque bolts to 9 to 12
                    lbf-ft (12 to 16 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If sound insulation was removed from the hood mirror mounting area, glue the sound
                    insulation back into position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
